<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910409-0105</DOCNO><DOCID>910409-0105.</DOCID><HL>   Novell's Favorable Settlement</HL><DATE>04/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   NOVL</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><RE>UTAH (UT)</RE><LP>   PROVO, Utah -- Novell Inc. said it reached a favorableout-of-court agreement in a copyright infringement suitagainst Reliable Data Systems.   The agreement resolves a suit Novell filed Feb. 20 inwhich the software firm obtained a temporary restrainingorder to prevent Reliable, a value-added reseller, fromcontinuing to sell unauthorized versions of Novell's NetWarenetwork operating system. Reliable had sold a number of suchpackages with unlicensed NetWare products, according toNovell.</LP><TEXT>   Under its agreement with Novell, Reliable will not sellany more unauthorized NetWare systems and is to pay Novell a&quot;six-figure&quot; damage settlement. The actual amount wasn'tdisclosed. &quot;We've made some mistakes in not recognizing thesubtleties of copyright infringement,&quot; said Steve Baldwin,president of Reliable, which is based in Baltimore.</TEXT></DOC>